title: Palmer's Sand Springs Criterium- OK State age-based championship
description: Palmer's Sand Springs Criterium is a benefit for the non-profit Palmer Continuum of Care.
course:
Technical course with short, challenging climbs and a fast sprint finish located in downtown Sand Springs. The
course will be closed to traffic. Wheel pit will be along town triangle and accessible from two points. Wheels in Wheels out. Start/
Finish is located at N. McKinley and E. Broadway in Sand Springs.
registration:
Race day registration opens at 7:00am and will be open all day.**Race Day Registration increases by $10.00.
Registration closes 15 minutes before each race. $15 for each additional race. One-day and annual USAC licenses will be on sale.
Online registration at www.usacycling.org. Online registration closes midnight May 13th.
notes:
Palmer’s Sand Springs Criterium is hosting Age Based Oklahoma Championships only. State
Championship Jerseys will be offered in the age groups listed below. Ages are based on the racing age of your 2016 USA Cycling
license. You must race your age group and are only eligible for championship and prize money/awards for your age group.
Out of state riders and racers using a one day license are not eligible for State Champions, but may race for prize money/awards.
All races not listed below will not be awarded State Championship Jerseys State Championship Categories Men 30-39, 40-49, 50-59
and 60+ Men U23 (age 19-23) Juniors (both women and men) 9-14, 15-16 and 17-18 Women 40+.
directions:
From Tulsa: US 412 East toward Enid/Sand Springs 6.1 miles, Exit Adams Rd onto 2nd street, Follow signs to event
parking. From OKC: Exit I-44 at Exit #215/Ok97 toward Sand Springs/Sapulpa, left on N 9th ST [Ok-97] follow for 8.6 miles to 2nd
street. Right on 2nd to McKinley.

title: Oklahoma City Pro-Am Fondo
description: Fun yet challenging event for cyclists of all ages and abilities.
course: The District Tour takes riders on a tour through many of OKC's favorite districts such as Film Row, Midtown, Automobile Alley, Plaza, Paseo, Uptown 23rd and many more.  Both the 30 & 58 mile routes take riders east of the city where they can enjoy the some great OK views & challenging rolling terrain. The Fondo offers a route option for riders of all ability levels.  We are presenting a 12 mile district tour, a 30 mile mid-distance ride, and a 58 mile trek touring the countryside as well as OKC neighborhoods.  All three distance options begin and finish at the center of Saturday's racing venue, Film Row, so you won't miss out on any of the high-octane criterium racing!
notes: So you don't feel up to leaping into the fray of the races - we get it.  Maybe you would prefer a self-paced, leisure tour of of OKC's prominent districts & neighborhoods, or maybe you're craving an excuse to take your steed out for a couple of hours on a supported ride exploring the greater metro area.  No matter your fancy, we have just the thing for you:  the OKC ProAm Fondo.

title: Bixby Bicycles - Oklahoma State Championship Road Race (age
Tour de Tryke Twilight Criterium
description: Tour de Trykes Twilight Criterium is in it's sixth year. Each year the race format has been changed to reflect the wants and needs of the riders. This year we are lengthening the race for all riders, something that has been asked for.
course: The course is a figure eight with one demanding uphill. This course is very fast with wide turns which will allow the riders maximum safety. Parts of the surface have been recently repaved.
registration: Registration is online through USA Cycling. Registration can be done onsite the day of, however it is recommended what riders register online to save registration fees. Multiple races can be entered depending upon category with multiple entry discount which will be refunded at number pick up.
directions: From the South on I- 35 Take hwy 412 West into Enid. From the north on I-35 take 412 West into Enid. Go North on Independence to race course, downtown Enid. Parking is located on perimeter of course.

title: Charley's Bike Lab Cross Race
description: This is a 1 day Cyclocross Race by the OKC Velo Bike Lab Team.
course: A flat and flowy course is a great intro into the Oklahoma Cyclocross Season! We start on a local Track and Field surface and then hit the Harrah High School grounds & cross country course for a fast race.
registration: Registration is Online and Day Off. Same Price for either. Details listed in the Flyer.

title: The Veterans Challenge
course: Rolling hills and back country. We will leave Broken Arrow, head south through Haskell, and then east to Muskogee. After reaching the VA hospital in Muskogee, riders will return the same route.

title: Family Fat Tire Festival

address.street: Lake Thunderbird State Park, 13101 Alameda Dr

description: Every fall, the Family Fat Tire Festival takes place on a Saturday 10 am -2 pm out at Lake Thunderbird State park Clear Bay mountain Bike Trails, off Highway 9 (14 miles East of I-35). Norman. The Family Fat Tire Festival is a FREE annual event that is presented by Team Phoenix racing, along with Norman Regional Health System and Bike one. We make this a family friendly community event, where they get to experience bicycle trail riding that is fun for the whole family at one of Oklahoma’s premier mountain bike trails, Clear Bay at Lake Thunderbird in Norman, Oklahoma. We teach bike safety awareness, give guided bike rides on marked trails with a lead and sweep team members and much more.
directions: Lake Thunderbird State park Clear Bay mountain Bike Trails, off Highway 9 (14 miles East of I-35). Norman.
